his conclusions are the workbooks in which Nietzsche first recorded his advances, especially the 1881 workbook which shows him gradually gaining insights into the two foundations of his mature thinking. The result is the most complete picture we’ve had yet of the philosopher’s development, one that gives us a Promethean Nietzsche, gaining knowledge even as he was expanding his thought to create new worlds.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aNietzsche, Friedrich Wilhelm,-1844-1900. 0aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aNietzsche’s Nachlass.  aNietzsche’s development.  aartist.  aautobiography.  aeternal return.  aphilosopher.  awill to power.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226488257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226488257/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles